CLARIFY  
We need a minimal hangman game in JavaScript.  
Key points:  
- A fixed list of candidate words.  
- One word is chosen at random and stored in a hidden array.  
- The same array is turned into underscores (one per letter).  
- On each user input (a single letter), every matching underscore is replaced by the letter.  
- No external libraries, no DOM; everything runs in Node via stdin/stdout.

APPROACH  
1. Naïve: scan the word on every guess with indexOf in a loop → O(n) per guess, trivial but acceptable for short words.  
2. Optimal: pre-compute a map letter → [indices] so each guess is O(k) where k = occurrences of the letter.  
We choose approach 2 because it is strictly better (O(k) vs O(n)) and keeps the code simple.

DATA STRUCTURE  
A plain object (hash map) `letterMap` whose keys are letters and whose values are arrays of indices.  
This is optimal because lookup is O(1) and we avoid repeated scans of the word.

CODE (self-contained, no built-ins beyond console & process)

```js
// hangman.js
function hangmanGame() {
  const words = ['javascript', 'nodejs', 'hangman', 'programming', 'computer'];
  const word = words[Math.floor(Math.random() * words.length)];
  const hidden = Array(word.length).fill('_');
  const letterMap = {};               // letter -> [indices]
  for (let i = 0; i < word.length; i++) {
    const c = word[i];
    (letterMap[c] = letterMap[c] || []).push(i);
  }

  console.log('Palabra:', hidden.join(' '));

  const readline = require('readline').createInterface({
    input: process.stdin,
    output: process.stdout
  });

  function ask() {
    readline.question('Ingresa una letra: ', letter => {
      const l = letter.toLowerCase();
      if (letterMap[l]) {
        letterMap[l].forEach(idx => hidden[idx] = l);
        console.log('¡Correcto! Palabra:', hidden.join(' '));
      } else {
        console.log('Incorrecto. Palabra:', hidden.join(' '));
      }

      if (!hidden.includes('_')) {
        console.log('¡Ganaste! La palabra era:', word);
        readline.close();
      } else {
        ask();
      }
    });
  }

  ask();
}

if (require.main === module) {
  hangmanGame();
}
```

ANALYSIS  
Time complexity: O(k) per guess where k = number of occurrences of the guessed letter (optimal).  
Space complexity: O(n) for the letter map plus hidden array, where n = word length.

TEST  
Run with:  
```bash
node hangman.js
```  
