# Dynamic RPC Health Checking vs Manual Blacklisting

You're absolutely right that **dynamic health checking is generally better** than manual blacklisting. Here's why:

## Problems with Manual Blacklisting

```typescript
// ❌ Manual approach - requires constant maintenance
const BLACKLISTED_RPCS = [
  'https://slow-rpc.example.com',
  'https://down-rpc.example.com',
  // Needs PR every time an RPC goes down or comes back up
];
```

**Issues:**
- RPCs can recover (you'd miss them)
- New RPCs can fail (you'd need constant updates)
- Different regions have different performance
- Doesn't adapt to real-time conditions

## Better: Dynamic Health Checking

```typescript
interface RPCHealthMetrics {
  url: string;
  latency: number;
  successRate: number;
  lastChecked: number;
  consecutiveFailures: number;
}

class DynamicRPCManager {
  private healthMetrics = new Map<string, RPCHealthMetrics>();
  private readonly MAX_FAILURES = 3;
  private readonly HEALTH_CHECK_INTERVAL = 60000; // 1 minute
  private readonly LATENCY_THRESHOLD = 2000; // 2 seconds

  constructor(private rpcUrls: string[]) {
    this.initializeMetrics();
    this.startHealthChecks();
  }

  private initializeMetrics() {
    this.rpcUrls.forEach(url => {
      this.healthMetrics.set(url, {
        url,
        latency: 0,
        successRate: 1,
        lastChecked: Date.now(),
        consecutiveFailures: 0
      });
    });
  }

  private async checkRPCHealth(url: string): Promise<void> {
    const start = Date.now();

    try {
      const response = await fetch(url, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          jsonrpc: '2.0',
          id: 1,
          method: 'eth_blockNumber',
          params: []
        }),
        signal: AbortSignal.timeout(5000) // 5s timeout
      });

      const latency = Date.now() - start;
      const metrics = this.healthMetrics.get(url)!;

      if (response.ok) {
        metrics.latency = latency;
        metrics.consecutiveFailures = 0;
        metrics.successRate = Math.min(1, metrics.successRate + 0.1);
      } else {
        this.handleFailure(url);
      }
    } catch (error) {
      this.handleFailure(url);
    }

    this.healthMetrics.get(url)!.lastChecked = Date.now();
  }

  private handleFailure(url: string) {
    const metrics = this.healthMetrics.get(url)!;
    metrics.consecutiveFailures++;
    metrics.successRate = Math.max(0, metrics.successRate - 0.2);
  }

  private startHealthChecks() {
    setInterval(() => {
      this.rpcUrls.forEach(url => this.checkRPCHealth(url));
    }, this.HEALTH_CHECK_INTERVAL);
  }

  getHealthyRPCs(): string[] {
    return Array.from(this.healthMetrics.values())
      .filter(metrics => 
        metrics.consecutiveFailures < this.MAX_FAILURES &&
        metrics.latency < this.LATENCY_THRESHOLD &&
        metrics.successRate > 0.5
      )
      .sort((a, b) => {
        // Sort by success rate and latency
        const scoreA = a.successRate / (a.latency + 1);
        const scoreB = b.successRate / (b.latency + 1);
        return scoreB - scoreA;
      })
      .map(m => m.url);
  }

  getBestRPC(): string | null {
    const healthy = this.getHealthyRPCs();
    return healthy[0] || null;
  }

  // Get metrics for monitoring
  getMetrics() {
    return Array.from(this.healthMetrics.values());
  }
}
```

