CLARIFY  
The third-party GLTF loader ignores the KHR_texture_transform extension, so the only way to keep a “tiled” (repeated) texture is to pre-bake the repeat into the geometry itself—i.e. multiply every UV coordinate by the repeat vector (uScale, vScale) before the scene is exported.

APPROACH  
1. CPU-side: clone the geometry, loop over the uv attribute and multiply every (u,v) by the repeat vector.  
   Time O(n) where n = number of vertices, Space O(n) for the cloned attribute.  
2. GPU-side: do nothing—KHR_texture_transform is already handled by Three.js, but the target loader will ignore it, so this is useless here.  

We choose approach 1 because it is the only one that survives the export pipeline when KHR_texture_transform is unsupported.

CODE (Three.js r150+, no external helpers beyond Three.js itself)

```js
/**
 * Bakes the material.repeat into the geometry UVs so the model
 * will tile correctly even when KHR_texture_transform is ignored.
 * @param {THREE.Mesh} mesh  – mesh whose geometry will be modified in place
 */
function bakeRepeatIntoUVs(mesh) {
  const geom = mesh.geometry;
  const mat  = mesh.material;

  // Accept either a single material or the first material of an array
  const material = Array.isArray(mat) ? mat[0] : mat;

  // Skip if no repeat or no UVs
  if (!material || !material.map || !geom.attributes.uv) return;

  const repeat = material.map.repeat;           // THREE.Vector2
  const uvAttr = geom.attributes.uv;
  const uvs = uvAttr.array;                     // Float32Array

  for (let i = 0; i < uvs.length; i += 2) {
    uvs[i]   *= repeat.x;   // u
    uvs[i+1] *= repeat.y;   // v
  }

  uvAttr.needsUpdate = true;
}
```

DATA STRUCTURE  
We mutate the existing `BufferAttribute` in place rather than allocating a new one—this keeps memory usage minimal (O(1) extra) and is safe because the geometry is about to be serialized anyway.

ANALYZE  
Time complexity: O(n) where n = number of UV pairs (≈ vertex count).  
Space complexity: O(1) extra—only scalar temporaries; the geometry itself is already allocated.

TEST / USAGE

```js
// Typical usage before GLTF export
const box = new THREE.Mesh(
  new THREE.BoxGeometry(1, 1, 1),
  new THREE.MeshStandardMaterial({ map: myTexture })
);
box.material.map.repeat.set(4, 2);   // 4×2 tiling
bakeRepeatIntoUVs(box);

// Now export
const exporter = new THREE.GLTFExporter();
exporter.parse(box.parent || box, gltf => {
  console.log(gltf); // GLTF with baked UVs
});
```

