### 1. CLARIFY
The goal is to refactor the `VideoSettings` React component to improve code quality, readability, and maintainability. The current implementation uses redundant state variables for values that can be derived directly from props, contains inline magic arrays, and uses verbose boolean logic and event handlers.

### 2. APPROACH
**Approach A (Current):** Uses `useState` to track `isYoutubeLink`, `isYoutubePrivacyModeEnabled`, and `showPlatformWarning`. These must be manually synced whenever the input changes, which is prone to bugs if `uploadedVideoUrl` changes externally.
**Approach B (Refactored - Optimal):** Remove derived state. Calculate these boolean flags on-the-fly during render based on `uploadedVideoUrl`. Extract hardcoded arrays to constants outside the component. Simplify event handler bindings and boolean returns.

### 3. WRITE

```tsx
import { AlertTriangle } from "lucide-react";
import { toast } from "react-hot-toast";

import { AdvancedOptionToggle } from "../../AdvancedOptionToggle";
import { Button } from "../../Button";
import { Input } from "../../Input";
import { Label } from "../../Label";
import {
  checkForYoutubePrivacyMode,
  checkForYoutubeUrl,
  extractYoutubeId,
  parseVideoUrl,
} from "../lib/utils";

const SUPPORTED_PLATFORMS = [
  "youtube.com",
  "youtu.be",
  "youtube-nocookie.com",
  "vimeo.com",
  "loom.com",
];

interface VideoSettingsProps {
  uploadedVideoUrl: string;
  setUploadedVideoUrl: (videoUrl: string) => void;
  onFileUpload: (uploadedUrl: string[] | undefined, fileType: "image" | "video") => void;
  videoUrl: string;
  setVideoUrlTemp: (videoUrl: string) => void;
}

export const VideoSettings = ({
  uploadedVideoUrl,
  setUploadedVideoUrl,
  onFileUpload,
  videoUrl,
  setVideoUrlTemp,
}: VideoSettingsProps) => {
  // 1. Derived variables (No need for useState)
  const isYoutubeLink = checkForYoutubeUrl(uploadedVideoUrl);
  const isYoutubePrivacyModeEnabled = checkForYoutubePrivacyMode(uploadedVideoUrl);

  const isSupportedPlatform = 
    !uploadedVideoUrl || 
    SUPPORTED_PLATFORMS.some((domain) => uploadedVideoUrl.includes(domain));
  const showPlatformWarning = !isSupportedPlatform;

  const isAddButtonDisabled = !uploadedVideoUrl.trim();
  const isVideoSaved = uploadedVideoUrl && videoUrl === uploadedVideoUrl;

  // 2. Simplified Handlers
  const toggleYoutubePrivacyMode = () => {
    const videoId = extractYoutubeId(uploadedVideoUrl);
    if (!videoId) {
      toast.error("Invalid YouTube URL");
      return;
    }

    // Toggle based on current derived state
    const newUrl = isYoutubePrivacyModeEnabled
      ? `https://www.youtube.com/embed/${videoId}`
      : `https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/${videoId}`;

    setUploadedVideoUrl(newUrl);
    if (videoUrl) {
      onFileUpload([newUrl], "video");
    }
  };

  const handleAddVideo = (e: React.MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const parsedUrl = parseVideoUrl(uploadedVideoUrl);
    if (parsedUrl) {
      setUploadedVideoUrl(parsedUrl);
      onFileUpload([parsedUrl], "video");
    } else {
      toast.error("Url not supported");
    }
  };

  const handleRemoveVideo = (e: React.MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setVideoUrlTemp("");
    onFileUpload([], "video");
  };

  const handleVideoUrlChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    setUploadedVideoUrl(e.target.value);
  };

  return (
    <form className="flex flex-col space-y-4">
      <Label>Video URL (Youtube, Vimeo or Loom)</Label>
      <div className="flex h-10 items-center space-x-2">
        <Input
          className="w-full"
          placeholder="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"
          value={uploadedVideoUrl}
          onChange={handleVideoUrlChange}
        />
        {isVideoSaved ? (
          <Button variant="darkCTA" onClick={handleRemoveVideo}>
            Remove
          </Button>
        ) : (
          <Button variant="darkCTA" onClick={handleAddVideo} disabled={isAddButtonDisabled}>
            Add
          </Button>
        )}
      </div>

      {showPlatformWarning && (
        <div className="flex items-center space-x-2 rounded-md border bg-slate-100 p-2 text-sm">
          <AlertTriangle className="h-4 w-4" />
          <p>Please enter a valid Youtube, Vimeo or Loom URL</p>
        </div>
      )}

      {isYoutubeLink && (
        <AdvancedOptionToggle
          htmlId="closeOnNumberOfResponse"
          isChecked={isYoutubePrivacyModeEnabled}
          onToggle={toggleYoutubePrivacyMode}
          title="YouTube Privacy Mode"
          description="Keeps user tracking to a minimum"
          childBorder={true}
        />
      )}
    </form>
  );
};
```

### 5. EXPLAIN
*   **Removed Derived State**: Removed `useState` for `isYoutubeLink`, `isYoutubePrivacyModeEnabled`, and `showPlatformWarning`. React components re-render when props change. Calculating these on the fly guarantees they are never out of sync with `uploadedVideoUrl`.
*   **Extracted Constants**: Moved the supported domains array outside the component so it isn't recreated on every render.
*   **Simplified Boolean Logic**: Changed `uploadedVideoUrl.trim() !== "" ? false : true` to simply `!uploadedVideoUrl.trim()`.
*   **Cleaned up JSX Event Handlers**: Changed `onChange={(e) => handleVideoUrlChange(e)}` to `onChange={handleVideoUrlChange}`. Passing the function reference directly is cleaner and avoids creating anonymous functions on every render.
*   **Extracted Render Logic**: Created `isVideoSaved` to make the ternary operator in the JSX much easier to read.

### 6. ANALYZE
*   **Time Complexity**: $O(N)$ where $N$ is the length of the URL string (due to string matching/parsing operations during render). This is optimal and negligible for UI rendering.
*   **Space Complexity**: $O(1)$ auxiliary space. We removed the unnecessary React state hooks, reducing memory overhead per component instance.

### 7. TEST
